.TH simple_shell 1 "April 2025" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a minimal UNIX command-line interpreter (shell) written in C, created as part of a learning project at Holberton School.

The shell reads commands from the standard input and executes them. It supports basic functionalities such as running system commands, handling arguments, using the PATH variable, and executing a few built-in commands.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
\fBPrompt\fR
Displays a prompt \fB$\fR where the user can type commands.

.TP
\fBExecute Commands\fR
Accepts standard UNIX commands and executes them using the \fBexecve\fR system call.

.TP
\fBArguments\fR
Supports commands with arguments (e.g., \fBls -l /tmp\fR).

.TP
\fBPATH Handling\fR
Searches for commands in the directories listed in the PATH environment variable.

.TP
\fBBuilt-in Commands\fR
Supports the following built-in commands:
.RS
.IP \fBexit\fR
Exit the shell.
.IP \fBenv\fR
Display the current environment variables.
.RE

.TP
\fBError Handling\fR
Handles errors such as:
- command not found
- permission denied
- failed fork or execve

.SH USAGE
.TP
To run the shell, compile the project and execute:
.B
./hsh

.TP
Examples:
.B
$ ls -l
.br
$ /bin/ls
.br
$ env
.br
$ exit

.SH FILES
.TP
.B main.c
Entry point of the shell.
.TP
.B exec.c
Handles command execution and process creation.
.TP
.B builtins.c
Implements built-in commands such as \fBexit\fR and \fBenv\fR.
.TP
.B utils.c
Contains helper functions like string parsing and memory management.
.TP
.B shell.h
Header file containing macros, structures, and function prototypes.

